<p>If you look at the currencies listed above you would discover that they are listed in pairs. Among those pairs of Currencies. The&nbsp;<strong>F</strong>irst Currency within the pair is called&nbsp;<strong>BASE CURRENCY&nbsp;</strong>while the&nbsp;<strong>S</strong>econd Currency within the pair is called&nbsp;<strong>QUOTE CURRENCY</strong>.</p>
<p><strong>Example</strong>&nbsp;<strong>EURUSD</strong></p>
