<li><strong>*USDCHF</strong></li>
</ul>
<p>Swis Franc is stronger than USD&nbsp;</p>
<p>When you see these few exceptions don&rsquo;t bother too much about why the weaker one is written first even though it&rsquo;s quite glaring that the Quote is Stronger. What you need to do is look at those numbers beside it (Picture 4). All the numbers that starts with 0.yyyyy (ie Zero point something) are exceptions. In them the Quote is stronger. It doesn&rsquo;t affect your Trading. It&rsquo;s just for knowledge sake.</p>
<p>However apart from those few exceptions generally in Forex the Base is always stronger than the Quote.</p>',
